---
title: Cranberry Pineapple Pork Chops with a Potato Cauliflower Mash and Green Beans
description: Cranberries and pineapple may seem like opposites. One is associated with New England’s cool climes while the other is most likely to be found at a Hawaiian luau. But when they meet in the middle, the result is a fantastically fruit-ful sauce that tastes amazing on pork. Add a cauliflower and potato mash to the side along with some green beans, and you’ve got a produce-filled meal that’s sure to be a hit in every state.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5afb3ef5ae08b54f3e77b092-7fd5c120.jpg
